{"id":65937,"title":"[Sexual health for patients suffering from cancer].","abstract":"Patients suffering from cancer generally see their sex life deteriorate. Their self-image, the way their body is seen and their relationships with others are profoundly changed. Inviting the patient to evoke their difficulties helps them to regain a fulfilling sex life despite the disease.","date":"2014-04-25","categories":"Male Urogenital Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24761521","annotations":[{"name":"Sex","weight":0.816331,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sex"},{"name":"Human sexual activity","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_sexual_activity"},{"name":"Reproductive health","weight":0.801318,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reproductive_health"},{"name":"Health","weight":0.765294,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.721318,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Human sexuality","weight":0.681894,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_sexuality"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.669249,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Suffering","weight":0.646869,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suffering"},{"name":"Cancer","weight":0.378001,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer"}]}
